{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs offer several advantages, including enhanced multimodal data processing for improved assessment accuracy [25], interactive communication methods like human-in-the-loop to create more configurable health agents [4], and the potential for fine-tuning domain-specific purpose based on general models to reduce costs [39,44].",
    "However, most work using LLMs to detect mental health focuses on tasks of single modality data such as Mental-LLM [44] and EEG-GPT [21], and the exploration of LLMs in evaluating multimodal sensing data for mental health remains limited.",
    "Moreover, existing multimodal LLMs have been developed primarily using audio and video modalities.",
    "They may lack the capabilities in handling other types of data, such as EEG and other physiological signals which play a crucial role [12] in mental health assessment.",
    "Among various physiological signals, EEG is particularly valuable, providing high-frequency data that accurately assesses conditions such as depression, mood, and stress levels [5]."
  ]
}